  "original_title": "Sri Lanka given US$4.0bn dollars of support from India: envoy",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka given US$4.0bn dollars of support from India: envoy",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 India has so far given Sri Lanka about 4.0 billion US dollars in financing in 2022, High Commissioner Gopal Bagley told reporters as a second consignment of fertilizer landed in Colombo financed by a credit line from his country.",
        "A shipment of 21,000 metric tonnes of fertilizer landed in Colombo on August 22, financed by the Indian credit line. India has already supplied 44,000 metric tonnes of fertilizer.",
        "\u201cThis is for the people of Sri Lanka. This is fo the farmers of Sri Lanka,\u201d High Commissioner Gopal Bagley told reporters.",
        "\u201cIndia has so far given Sri Lanka about 4.0 billion dollars of support.\u201d",
        "India has given 500 million US dollar credit line for fuel and 1,000 billion dollars in credit line for other imports including fertilizer.",
        "The import credit lines when fully re-imbursed by the private sector also allows budget support.",
        "In addition India has delayed about 200 to 300 million US dollars in import payments due under the Asian clearing union allowing the central bank to use it.",
        "Sri Lanka ran into the worst currency crisis in the history of the country\u2019s intermediate regime central bank after two year of money printing and a failed float with a surrender requirement (forced dollar sales to the central bank).",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s economists got the power to create forex shortages, high inflation and severe economic crisis with the setting up of an intermediate regime central bank (soft-peg) in August 1950.",
        "Forex shortages and currency crises are a problem associated with soft-pegs (central banks which operate a policy rate and collects reserves by targeting an exchange rate) which is not found in hard pegs or clean floats.",
        "Once the credibility of the peg has been lost due to money printing (mainly open market operations), economic activity has to be smashed with extra high interest rates to reduce outflows and end money printing.",
        "Sri Lanka has been intervening in fore markets with Indian money but economic activity is rapidly falling after rates went up and private credit slowed. (Colombo/Aug23/2022)"
      ],
